benchmarks.name: Recursive Fibonacci
benchmarks.description: Naive recursive fibonacci. Measures function call overhead and recursion depth.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To fib (n: Int) -> Int:
    If n is less than 2:
        Return n.
    Return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show fib(n).

benchmarks.name: Sieve of Eratosthenes
benchmarks.description: Classic prime sieve. Measures indexed array mutation, tight loops, and conditional branching.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To sieve (limit: Int) -> Int:
    Let mutable flags be a new Seq of Bool.
    Let mutable i be 0.
    While i is at most limit:
        Push false to flags.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Let mutable count be 0.
    Set i to 2.
    While i is at most limit:
        If item (i + 1) of flags equals false:
            Set count to count + 1.
            Let mutable j be i * i.
            While j is at most limit:
                Set item (j + 1) of flags to true.
                Set j to j + i.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Return count.

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let limit be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show sieve(limit).

benchmarks.name: Collection Operations
benchmarks.description: Hash map insert and lookup. Measures hash computation, allocation pressure, and cache behavior.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable m be a new Map of Int to Int with capacity n.
Let mutable i be 1.
While i is less than n + 1:
    Set item i of m to i * 2.
    Set i to i + 1.
Let mutable found be 0.
Set i to 1.
While i is less than n + 1:
    If item i of m equals i * 2:
        Set found to found + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show found.

benchmarks.name: String Assembly
benchmarks.description: String concatenation and assembly. Measures allocator throughput and GC pressure.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable result be "" with capacity n * 6.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set result to result + i + " ".
    Set i to i + 1.
Let count: Int be Escape to Rust:
    result.chars().filter(|c| *c == ' ').count() as i64
Show count.

benchmarks.name: Bubble Sort
benchmarks.description: O(n^2) bubble sort. Measures nested loops, indexed array mutation, and swap patterns.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int.
Let mutable seed be 42.
Let mutable i be 0.
While i is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 4294967296.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 32768 to arr.
    Set i to i + 1.
Set i to 0.
While i is less than n - 1:
    Let mutable j be 1.
    While j is at most n - 1 - i:
        Let a be item j of arr.
        Let b be item (j + 1) of arr.
        If a is greater than b:
            Set item j of arr to b.
            Set item (j + 1) of arr to a.
        Set j to j + 1.
    Set i to i + 1.
Show item 1 of arr.

benchmarks.name: Ackermann Function
benchmarks.description: Ackermann(3, m). Measures extreme recursion depth and stack frame overhead.
benchmarks.logos_source:
## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To ackermann (m: Int) and (n: Int) -> Int:
    If m equals 0:
        Return n + 1.
    If n equals 0:
        Return ackermann(m - 1, 1).
    Return ackermann(m - 1, ackermann(m, n - 1)).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Show ackermann(3, n).
